│ 12612 Syntax:                                                               │
│ 12613 """""""                                                               │
│ 12614                                                                       │
│ 12615 ::                                                                    │
│ 12616                                                                       │
│ 12617       <result> = select [fast-math flags] selty <cond>, <ty> <val1>,  │
│ <ty> <val2>             ; yields ty                                         │
│ 12618                                                                       │
│ 12619       selty is either i1 or {<N x i1>}                                │
│ 12620                                                                       │
│ 12621 Overview:                                                             │
│ 12622 """""""""                                                             │
│ 12623                                                                       │
│ 12624 The '``select``' instruction is used to choose one value based on a   │
│ 12625 condition, without IR-level branching.                                │
│ 12626                                                                       │
│ 12627 Arguments:                                                            │
│ 12628 """"""""""                                                            │
│ 12629                                                                       │
│ 12630 The '``select``' instruction requires an 'i1' value or a vector of    │
│ 'i1'                                                                        │
│ 12631 values indicating the condition, and two values of the same           │
│ :ref:`first                                                                 │
│ 12632 class <t_firstclass>` type.                                           │
│ 12633                                                                       │
│ 12634 #. The optional ``fast-math flags`` marker indicates that the select  │
│ has one or more                                                             │
│ 12635    :ref:`fast-math flags <fastmath>`. These are optimization hints to │
│ enable                                                                      │
│ 12636    otherwise unsafe floating-point optimizations. Fast-math flags are │
│ only valid                                                                  │
│ 12637    for selects that return :ref:`supported floating-point types       │
│ 12638    <fastmath_return_types>`.                                          │
│ 12639                                                                       │
│ 12640 Semantics:                                                            │
│ 12641 """"""""""                                                            │
│ 12642                                                                       │
│ 12643 If the condition is an i1 and it evaluates to 1, the instruction      │
│ returns                                                                     │
│ 12644 the first value argument; otherwise, it returns the second value      │
│ 12645 argument.                                                             │
│ 12646                                                                       │
│ 12647 If the condition is a vector of i1, then the value arguments must be  │
│ 12648 vectors of the same size, and the selection is done element by        │
│ element.                                                                    │
│ 12649                                                                       │
│ 12650 If the condition is an i1 and the value arguments are vectors of the  │
│ 12651 same size, then an entire vector is selected.                         │
│ 12652                                                                       │
│ 12653 Example:                                                              │
│ 12654 """"""""                                                              │
│ 12655                                                                       │
│ 12656 .. code-block:: llvm                                                  │
│ 12657                                                                       │
│ 12658       %X = select i1 true, i8 17, i8 42          ; yields i8:17       │
│ 12659                                                                       │
│ 12660                                                                       │
│ 12661 .. _i_freeze:                                                         │
│ 12662                                                                       │
│ 12663 '``freeze``' Instruction                                              │
│ 12664 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^                                              │
│ 12665                                                                       │
│ 12666 Syntax:                                                               │
│ 12667 """""""                                                               │
│ 12668                                                                       │
│ 12669 ::                                                                    │
│ 12670                                                                       │
│ 12671       <result> = freeze ty <val>    ; yields ty:result                │
│ 12672                                                                       │
│ 12673 Overview:                                                             │
│ 12674 """""""""                                                             │
│ 12675                                                                       │
│ 12676 The '``freeze``' instruction is used to stop propagation of           │
│ 12677 :ref:`undef <undefvalues>` and :ref:`poison <poisonvalues>` values.   │
│ 12678                                                                       │
│ 12679 Arguments:                                                            │
│ 12680 """"""""""                                                            │
│ 12681                                                                       │
│ 12682 The '``freeze``' instruction takes a single argument.                 │
│ 12683                                                                       │
│ 12684 Semantics:                                                            │
│ 12685 """"""""""                                                            │
│ 12686                                                                       │
│ 12687 If the argument is ``undef`` or ``poison``, '``freeze``' returns an   │
│ 12688 arbitrary, but fixed, value of type '``ty``'.                         │
│ 12689 Otherwise, this instruction is a no-op and returns the input          │
│ argument.                                                                   │
│ 12690 All uses of a value returned by the same '``freeze``' instruction are │
│ 12691 guaranteed to always observe the same value, while different          │
│ '``freeze``'                                                                │
│ 12692 instructions may yield different values.                              │
│ 12693                                                                       │
│ 12694 While ``undef`` and ``poison`` pointers can be frozen, the result is  │
│ a                                                                           │
│ 12695 non-dereferenceable pointer. See the                                  │
│ 12696 :ref:`Pointer Aliasing Rules <pointeraliasing>` section for more      │
│ information.                                                                │
│ 12697 If an aggregate value or vector is frozen, the operand is frozen      │
│ element-wise.                                                               │
│ 12698 The padding of an aggregate isn't considered, since it isn't visible  │
│ 12699 without storing it into memory and loading it with a different type.  │
│ 12700                                                                       │
│ 12701                                                                       │
│ 12702 Example:                                                              │
│ 12703 """"""""                                                              │
│ 12704                                                                       │
│ 12705 .. code-block:: text                                                  │
│ 12706                                                                       │
│ 12707       %w = i32 undef                                                  │
│ 12708       %x = freeze i32 %w                                              │
│ 12709       %y = add i32 %w, %w         ; undef                             │
│ 12710       %z = add i32 %x, %x         ; even number because all uses of   │
│ %x observe                                                                  │
│ 12711                                   ; the same value                    │
│ 12712       %x2 = freeze i32 %w                                             │
│ 12713       %cmp = icmp eq i32 %x, %x2  ; can be true or false              │
│ 12714                                                                       │
│ 12715       ; example with vectors                                          │
│ 12716       %v = <2 x i32> <i32 undef, i32 poison>                          │
│ 12717       %a = extractelement <2 x i32> %v, i32 0    ; undef              │
│ 12718       %b = extractelement <2 x i32> %v, i32 1    ; poison             │
│ 12719       %add = add i32 %a, %a                      ; undef              │
│ 12720                                                                       │
│ 12721       %v.fr = freeze <2 x i32> %v                ; element-wise       │
│ freeze                                                                      │
│ 12722       %d = extractelement <2 x i32> %v.fr, i32 0 ; not undef          │
│ 12723       %add.f = add i32 %d, %d                    ; even number        │
│ 12724                                                                       │
│ 12725       ; branching on frozen value                                     │
│ 12726       %poison = add nsw i1 %k, undef   ; poison                       │
│ 12727       %c = freeze i1 %poison                                          │
│ 12728       br i1 %c, label %foo, label %bar ; non-deterministic branch to  │
│ %foo or %bar                                                                │
│ 12729                                                                       │
│ 12730                                                                       │
│ 12731 .. _i_call:                                                           │
│ 12732                                                                       │
│ 12733 '``call``' Instruction                                                │
│ 12734 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^                                                │
│ 12735                                                                       │
│ 12736 Syntax:                                                               │
│ 12737 """""""                                                               │
│ 12738                                                                       │
│ 12739 ::                                                                    │
│ 12740                                                                       │
│ 12741       <result> = [tail | musttail | notail ] call [fast-math flags]   │
│ [cconv] [ret attrs] [addrspace(<num>)]                                      │
│ 12742                  <ty>|<fnty> <fnptrval>(<function args>) [fn attrs] [ │
│ operand bundles ]                                                           │
│ 12743                                                                       │
│ 12744 Overview:                                                             │
│ 12745 """""""""                                                             │
│ 12746                                                                       │
│ 12747 The '``call``' instruction represents a simple function call.         │
│ 12748                                                                       │
│ 12749 Arguments:                                                            │
│ 12750 """"""""""                                                            │
│ 12751                                                                       │
│ 12752 This instruction requires several arguments:                          │
│ 12753                                                                       │
│ 12754 #. The optional ``tail`` and ``musttail`` markers indicate that the   │
│ optimizers                                                                  │
│ 12755    should perform tail call optimization. The ``tail`` marker is a    │
│ hint that                                                                   │
│ 12756    `can be ignored <CodeGenerator.html#tail-call-optimization>`_. The │
│ 12757    ``musttail`` marker means that the call must be tail call          │
│ optimized in order                                                          │
│ 12758    for the program to be correct. This is true even in the presence   │
│ of                                                                          │
│ 12759    attributes like "disable-tail-calls". The ``musttail`` marker      │
│ provides these                                                              │
│ 12760    guarantees:                                                        │
│ 12761                                                                       │
│ 12762    #. The call will not cause unbounded stack growth if it is part of │
│ a                                                                           │
│ 12763       recursive cycle in the call graph.                              │
│ 12764    #. Arguments with the :ref:`inalloca <attr_inalloca>` or           │
│ 12765       :ref:`preallocated <attr_preallocated>` attribute are forwarded │
│ in place.                                                                   │
│ 12766    #. If the musttail call appears in a function with the ``"thunk"`` │
│ attribute                                                                   │
│ 12767       and the caller and callee both have varargs, then any           │
│ unprototyped                                                                │
│ 12768       arguments in register or memory are forwarded to the callee.    │
│ Similarly,                                                                  │
│ 12769       the return value of the callee is returned to the caller's      │
│ caller, even                                                                │
│ 12770       if a void return type is in use.                                │
│ 12771                                                                       │
│ 12772    Both markers imply that the callee does not access allocas,        │
│ va_args, or                                                                 │
│ 12773    byval arguments from the caller. As an exception to that, an       │
│ alloca or byval                                                             │
│ 12774    argument may be passed to the callee as a byval argument, which    │
│ can be                                                                      │
│ 12775    dereferenced inside the callee. For example:                       │
│ 12776                                                                       │
│ 12777 .. code-block:: llvm                                                  │
│ 12778                                                                       │
│ 12779       declare void @take_byval(ptr byval(i64))                        │
│ ---------------------------------------                                     │
